when books became important

00:02:36.260 --> 00:02:37.920
in your life for the first time?

00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:42.580
I was lucky enough to have a father
who read to me before I could read.

00:02:42.580 --> 00:02:45.210
&gt;&gt; Ken Burns: My answer is
that I don't remember a time

00:02:45.210 --> 00:02:48.380
when books weren't important
to me because I was read

00:02:48.380 --> 00:02:52.560
to from the moment I was
born by both my parents

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:54.440
and it became a huge part of it.

00:02:54.440 --> 00:03:01.070
And though my mother was sick I was
able to also spend a lot of time,

00:03:01.070 --> 00:03:05.240
very precious time, with my father
who would read me long novels

00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:07.880
that would take several
weeks to read,

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:09.910 position:56%
books that he had gotten as a child.

00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:11.950
