pretty honest with ourselves.

00:15:31.070 --> 00:15:36.000
This is our original sin, we
know as a country that we,

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:41.280
where we were founded and when,
July 4, 1776 in Philadelphia

00:15:41.280 --> 00:15:43.120
and we know what our catechism is,

00:15:43.120 --> 00:15:44.970
it's the second sentence
of the declaration.

00:15:44.970 --> 00:15:47.830
It begins, we hold these
truths to be self-evident

00:15:47.830 --> 00:15:49.470
that all men are created equal.

00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:51.620
Yet I have to stop right
there, a third of the way

00:15:51.620 --> 00:15:53.630
through that wonderful sentence,

00:15:53.630 --> 00:15:56.830
arguably the second greatest
sentence in the English language,

00:15:56.830 --> 00:16:01.560 position:56%
the first is obviously I love you,
but after that you'd be hard pressed

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:06.080
to find a better statement,
sentence, because the guy who wrote

00:16:06.080 --> 00:16:10.110 position:56%
that owned more than 100 human
beings and didn't see the hypocrisy,

00:16:10.110 --> 00:16:13.350
the contradiction or see fit
in his lifetime to free any

00:16:13.350 --> 00:16:16.550
of those human beings and set
in motion American narrative,

00:16:16.550 --> 00:16:18.830
symbolically but also literally,

00:16:18.830 --> 00:16:20.950
that is constantly
struggling to deal with that.

00:16:20.950 --> 00:16:25.220
And as what's going on today, it
happens to be Charlotte or Tulsa

00:16:25.220 --> 00:16:29.550
